call(address,uint256,bytes).details: Only the contract owner can call this function.Reverted calls will result in a revert.

params._data: The calldata to send with the call.
params._to: The address of the contract to call.
params._value: The amount of Ether to send with the call.

executeArbitrage(address,address,uint256.details: Only the contract owner can call this function.

params.firstPairAddress: Address of the first Uniswap V2 pair.
params.secondPairAddress: Address of the second Uniswap V2 pair.

params.firstPairData: Struct containing data about the first Uniswap V2 pair.
params.secondPairData: Struct containing data about the second Uniswap V2 pair.

returns._0: amountIn, the optimal amount to trade to arbitrage two v2 pairs.

params.reserveIn: The reserve of the input token.
params.reserveOut: The reserve of the output token.

params.pair: The Uniswap V2 pair to retrieve data for.

returns._0: A IPairReserves.PairReserves struct containing price and reserve data for the given pair.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawETHToOwner().details: Only the contract owner can call this function.

withdrawWETHToOwner().details: Only the contract owner can call this function.

call(address,uint256,bytes).notice: Executes a call to another contract with the provided data and value.

executeArbitrage(address,address,uint256.notice: Executes an arbitrage transaction between two Uniswap V2 pairs.Pair addresses need to be computed off-chain.

getAmountIn((uint256,uint256,uint256,boo.notice: Calculates the required input amount for the arbitrage transaction.

getAmountOut(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Calculates the output amount for a given input amount and reserves.

getPairData(address).notice: Retrieves price and reserve data for a given Uniswap V2 pair. Also checks which token is WETH.

withdrawETHToOwner().notice: Transfers all ETH held by the contract to the contract owner.

withdrawWETHToOwner().notice: Transfers all WETH held by the contract to the contract owner.
